<br>
It is way too easy to get items on EverQuest.  I mean really, I see characters with tons of uber shit!  Way too much gear.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I'm as guilty as the next guy of having my main twink my alts.  we all do it.  Those first 35 levels are boorrrrring!  But c'mon, I see 35th level warriors with 50+ level gear outdamaging 42nd level warriors!  I see some people constantly selling gear in the tunnel, you know who you are.  I'm talking about 15 or so good quality non-trade items a day.  Some of these people are just traders (buy from Joe, sell later at a higher price) but there just should not be that much loot available.<br>
<br>
And I'm truly sick of taking a new twink (say 20th level) into a dungeon (say UG) and doing /who and seeing something like this:<br>
52nd enchanter<br>
48th warrior<br>
48th rogue<br>
48th necromancer<br>
53rd shadow knight<br>
38th wizard<br>
etc<br>
etc<br>
<br>
there are 14 players in Upper Guk (and 1 that will get XP from the mobs there...)<br>
<br>
OK, so what to do about it?<br>
I would suggest:<br>
-more no-drop items.  You have to earn it to have it.<br>
<br>
-have items break.  That would be hillarious!  <br>
Joe: Hey, look at this UBERCLOAKOFEVERYTHING I got!<br>
Julie:  Wow, that's sweet!  How did you get it?<br>
Joe: Traded 2 SWEETSWORDSOFMASSIVEDAMAGE for it.<br>
Next day:  **your UBERCLOAKOFEVERYTHING broke**  OK, maybe that's too cruel.<br>
<br>
- trade skill items can be traded only 1 time then they become no-drop.<br>
<br>
-If you don't get XP from the mob, you don't get loot from the mob.<br>
<br>
OK, everyone can flame me and yell about how they camp forever to get XYZ item and it takes forever to get anything.  BTW, I have several twinks on different servers, so I'm as guilty as the next guy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukoneorcbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kone Orcbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/13/01 4:50:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There is way too much loot on the servers...</span><hr size=1> There does not seem to much Cobalt on this server. I have killed 25 Captains and 14 Callers of Sathir in KC and not seen Cobalt gauntlets or boots drop. (Also had about 6 of each KS'ed) I have been trying for almost four levels. I've seen Shamie armour and Rogue armour drop in there twice each. No Cobalt EVER!!! I think I've earned it by now. Where is it? Have you got a warrior twinked with it? Maybe you have it all...I'll buy it from you. Please????<br>
