s mid level economy after a while.  I dont know if theres really a good fix for this, bc it still takes a long time to camp an item and it would suck to have it decay on you.  I guess you gotta decide if an economy with integrity is worth all that player frustration, I think verant made the right call.  If you have items decay you have to also have them widely available no one is gonna want to spend 6 hrs to get something then have it decay.  So the other model is the UO model where items are plentiful but decay.  I dont think theres a wrong way to do it both models appeal to different types of gamers.  Merchant type people will have a roughish time of it in a eq system bc items constantly depreciate, but adventurers get to have unique items that they win themselves.  That said I have seen some merchant people have unbeleiveable success (I should link this guy on my old servers auctions, guildless level 12 necro, selling cobalt bp ect heh).  You just need to understand the economy and play it right, like any game I guess. <br>
<br>
 I dunno what Im saying really, I almost deleted this thing^^  I think the issue is a bit more complex than just &quot;there are too many items&quot; and that if there are its by design, and not nessesarily entirely a bad thing. <p>Procax
